<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D690346FFBC5E7DFF0F6C26FF03" authority="Tavakilian &amp; Santos-Silva, 2019" authorityName="Tavakilian &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,531,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Isomerida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fourneti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5E7DFF0F6C26FF03" box="[322,531,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Isomerida fourneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5D25FF0F6C46FF03" bold="true" box="[538,627,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23957830346FFBC5D25FF0F6C46FF03" box="[538,627,223,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D690346FFBC5DCEFF316A1FFF03" authority="(Laporte, 1840)" authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1840" baseAuthorityName="Laporte" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[753,1066,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Isomerida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5DCEFF316D45FF03" box="[753,880,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">I. albicollis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B1B0346FFBC5C40FF306A17FF03" author="Laporte, F. L. N." box="[895,1058,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" refId="ref11465" refString="Laporte, F. L. N. (1840) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes Coleopteres. Fol. 2. P. Dumenil, Paris, 563 pp." type="book" year="1840">Laporte, 1840</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B1B0346FFBC5BF0FF0F6EC7FEE6" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." pageId="5" pageNumber="512" pagination="4 - 296" refId="ref11796" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2014 b) Subfamilia Lamiinae. Tribo Hemilophini. Parte II. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Taxonomia. Fol. 14. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 4 - 296." type="book chapter" year="2014">Martins &amp; Galileo (2014b)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D690346FFBC5FC2FED56F49FEE6" baseAuthorityName="Laporte" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[253,380,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Isomerida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5FC2FED56F49FEE6" box="[253,380,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">I. albicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows notable variation in the color of integument and pubescence. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D690346FFBC5BD5FED56B79FEE7" authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="1996" box="[1258,1356,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Isomerida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="invicta">
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5BD5FED56B79FEE7" box="[1258,1356,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">I. invicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D690346FFBC5FE8FEF96F6FFEBB" baseAuthorityName="Laporte" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[215,346,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Isomerida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5FE8FEF96F6FFEBB" box="[215,346,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">I. albicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by structural features: prothoracic lateral tubercle very noticeable, distance between apices of tubercles distinctly wider than basal prothoracic width; distance between upper eye lobes shorter than 2.5 times width of a lobe; ventral erect setae on antennomeres shorter and distinctly spare at antennomere V (
<figureCitation id="13452A6F0346FFBC5A31FEBF6B61FE73" box="[1294,1364,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1–3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1942,1964]" captionTargetBox="[189,1407,197,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1407,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1–3, Guyarolea lalannecassoui sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, lateral habitus; 3, head, frontal view. 4–7, Isomerida fourneti sp. nov., holotype male: 4, head, frontal view; 5, dorsal habitus; 6, lateral habitus; 7, antennomere V. 8–12, Isomerida albicollis, male: 8–10, dorsal habitus; 11–12, antennomere V." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2585301/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D690346FFBC5AB3FEA16ECAFE56" baseAuthorityName="Laporte" baseAuthorityYear="1840" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Isomerida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5AB3FEA16ECAFE56" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">I. albicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13452A6F0346FFBC5E2EFE446FB2FE57" box="[273,391,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1–3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1942,1964]" captionTargetBox="[189,1407,197,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1407,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1–3, Guyarolea lalannecassoui sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, lateral habitus; 3, head, frontal view. 4–7, Isomerida fourneti sp. nov., holotype male: 4, head, frontal view; 5, dorsal habitus; 6, lateral habitus; 7, antennomere V. 8–12, Isomerida albicollis, male: 8–10, dorsal habitus; 11–12, antennomere V." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2585301/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Figs 8–10</figureCitation>
), the prothoracic lateral tubercle is less prominent, and the distance between apices of the tubercles is equal to about basal prothoracic width, distance between upper eye lobes equal to about 3.5 times width of a lobe (in some specimens wider), and ventral erect setae on antennomeres longer and abundant at antennomere V (
<figureCitation id="13452A6F0346FFBC5F81FE2F6F76FDE3" box="[190,323,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1–3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1942,1964]" captionTargetBox="[189,1407,197,1915]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1407,195,1934]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1–3, Guyarolea lalannecassoui sp. nov., holotype male: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, lateral habitus; 3, head, frontal view. 4–7, Isomerida fourneti sp. nov., holotype male: 4, head, frontal view; 5, dorsal habitus; 6, lateral habitus; 7, antennomere V. 8–12, Isomerida albicollis, male: 8–10, dorsal habitus; 11–12, antennomere V." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2585301/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Figs 11–12</figureCitation>
). Although the 
<typeStatus id="54C588480346FFBC5EC2FE2F6C6AFDE3" box="[509,607,511,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54C588480346FFBC5DA1FDD06CCBFDE3" box="[670,766,512,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D690346FFBC5C13FDD16DA6FDE3" authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="1996" box="[812,915,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Isomerida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="invicta">
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5C13FDD16DA6FDE3" box="[812,915,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">I. invicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are females (
<figureCitation id="13452A6F0346FFBC5B09FE2F6ABBFDE3" box="[1078,1166,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–21. 13" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[193,1399,195,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[187,1405,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 13–21. 13, Isomerida invicta, paratype female, dorsal habitus. 14–16, Lapazina arnaudi sp. nov., holotype male: 14, dorsal habitus; 15, lateral habitus; 16, head, frontal view. 17–18, Lapazina fuscipennis, male: 17, dorsal habitus; 18, ventral habitus. 19–21, Cendiunopsis garnieri sp. nov., holotype male: 19, head, frontal view; 20, dorsal habitus; 21, lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2585303/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
; see photograph of the 
<typeStatus id="54C588480346FFBC5FA8FDF46ECCFDC6" box="[151,249,548,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">holotype</typeStatus>
at 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B1B0346FFBC5E21FDF46C14FDC7" author="Lingafelter, S. W. &amp; Monne, M. A. &amp; Micheli, C. J. &amp; Nearns, E. H." box="[286,545,548,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" refId="ref11495" refString="Lingafelter, S. W., Monne, M. A., Micheli, C. J. &amp; Nearns, E. H. (2018) Online image database of cerambycoid primary types of the Smithsonian Institution. Available from: http: // SmithsonianCerambycidae. com / (accessed 22 October 2018)" type="url" year="2018">
Lingafelter 
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5E9CFDF56FE8FDC6" box="[419,477,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), it is possible to conclude that the new species is not the male of that species because the prothorax is notably transverse and the lateral tubercles are much more protruding.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC136EA0346FFBC5FF8FDBC6DEAFD53" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">
The inclusion of the new species in the key from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B1B0346FFBC5DD0FDBC6A28FD7E" author="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[751,1053,620,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" pagination="4 - 296" refId="ref11796" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2014 b) Subfamilia Lamiinae. Tribo Hemilophini. Parte II. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Taxonomia. Fol. 14. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 4 - 296." type="book chapter" year="2014">Martins &amp; Galileo (2014b)</bibRefCitation>
is not possible due to problems in the alternative of couplet “13” (dimensions and dorsal carina of the elytra).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36465610346FFBC5FF8FD646FD7FD0B" pageId="5" pageNumber="512" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC136EA0346FFBC5FF8FD646FD7FD0B" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis id="B90AEAF80346FFBC5FF8FD646F73FD36" bold="true" box="[199,326,692,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="512">Etymology</emphasis>
. In honor of Alain Fournet, phytopharmacologist colleague of the first author who generously offered this unique specimen.
</paragraph>
